arts.ttl: EXCLUSIVE: Chelsea go ‘all in’ for Liam Delap
arts.sum: Chelsea will do everything they can to sign Liam Delap from Ipswich Town in the summer, sources have told FootballTransfers. Chelsea’s form has collapsed over this period, with Cole Palmer’s goal drought further underlining the need for the Stamford Bridge side told find a goal-scoring solution.

arts.ttl: Ten-man Man Utd beat Ipswich in five-goal thriller
arts.sum: Harry Maguire secured 10-man Manchester United a first Premier League win since January, edging Ipswich Town 3-2 at Old Trafford. After a shaky defensive showing in the first half, United looked well-drilled in the second, throwing bodies on the line to make continuous blocks to end a run of three Premier League games without a win.

arts.ttl: Ipswich 'need to do better' and couldn't handle Man Utd - McKenna
arts.sum: Ipswich Town manager Kieran McKenna says he is "frustrated" and that his side "weren't able to handle" Manchester United in their 3-2 defeat at Old Trafford.
